}

Getting things to go left or right - float 

#left {
      float: left;
      width: 50%;
    }
    #right {
      float: right; 
      width: 40%;
    }

Center elements with margin: auto 

Colour theory: use split colour complements 
All elements have a default background-color of transparent. Our nav element currently appears to have a cyan background, because the element behind it has a background-color set to cyan. Add a background-color to the nav element so it uses the same cyan hue, 
but has 80% saturation and 25% lightness values to change its tone and shade.

nav {
    background-color: hsl(180, 80%, 25%);
  }
  
